Notes for Mac OSX Yosemite (10.10.3)

Running mongo db
1. open terminal
2. run "sudo -s" to run as root user
3. run "mongod"
4. you can run a client terminal with the "mongo" command

Running express app
1. open terminal
2. navigate to project directory
3. run "node app"
4. Open safari and go to localhost:1337